    "discriminators": [
     "Contact without release: sustained, high-centroid, low-crest, with partials that wander (large spectral_centroid_deviation_hz). Creaks, scrapes, squeaks. This is the friction archetype and it is the exact opposite of WOODImpt on every axis — crest factor, sustain_ratio and temporal centroid all invert.",
     "Against METALFric: same morphology, different colour. Wood friction is a stick-slip creak whose energy still concentrates in the low-mid band and which leaves no ringing tail behind the scrape; metal friction is brighter, more inharmonic, and rings on after contact ends.",
     "Against DOORCreak: physically the same event; DOORCreak simply asserts the creaking object is a door hinge. The explanation acknowledges the overlap in both directions."
